RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHESHIRE RACE 1 3M Timber CR: N/A. Allowance Purse 15000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Five-year-olds, 165 lbs.; older, 170 lbs. Non-winners of a timber stakes, allowed 5 lbs.; of a race over timber, 10 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COURT RULER (IRE) took command from the start, drew off to a sizeable margin, took out a rail second last fence, kept on and cleared the final fence cleanly, was geared down mid stretch, winning easily. MYSTIC STRIKE held second throughout and was no match for the winner. CRACKER FACTORY (GB) was unable to threaten and eased in the stretch. FLAMING SWORD (IRE) was unable to threaten and eased in stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Mystic Strike
ENTRY.COMMENT: held second throughout, no match for winner

ENTRY.NAME: Cracker Factory (GB)
ENTRY.COMMENT: unable to threaten, eased in stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Flaming Sword (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: unable to threaten, eased in stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Court Ruler (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: took command from start, gearing down mid stretch, easily

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHESHIRE RACE 2 3M Timber CR: N/A. Allowance Purse 10000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A TIMBER OR HURDLE STAKES IN 2022. To be ridden by apprentice riders. 170 lbs. Non-winners of two races over timber, allowed 5 lbs.; of a race, 10 lbs. Riders who have never won a race allowed 5 lbs. No oth er rider allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AWESOME ADRIAN was patiently ridden in second, sent to the lead 3 fences out, crossed wire first by a half length, DQ'd by stewards for going wrong side of a beacon (off course). MASTER SEVILLE stalked the leaders in third, closed well in the stretch, finishing second by a half length, subsequently declared the winner when others disqualified for going off course. MERCOEUR (FR) opened up a big lead after the 4th fence, tired badly 2nd last fence, DQ'd for going wrong side of a beacon (off course). POCKET TALK (IRE) was distanced on the final mile, and also DQ'd for going off course. Program numbers 2, 4 and 1 were unplaced for going off course and earned no purse money.

ENTRY.NAME: Pocket Talk (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: distanced final mile, DQ'd off course

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Awesome Adrian
ENTRY.COMMENT: patiently ridden in second, sent to lead 3 out, DQ'd off course

ENTRY.NAME: Master Seville
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked leaders, closed well in stretch, declared winner

ENTRY.NAME: Mercoeur (FR)
ENTRY.COMMENT: opened up big lead after 4th fence, tired badly 2nd last, DQ'd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHESHIRE RACE 3 3M Timber CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 10000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON OVER TIMBER. Five-year-olds, 160 lbs.; older, 165 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHOSEN MATE (IRE) led from start, took out rail two fences from home, kept on and held sway over rivals. RHYTHMIA closed and challenging two out when drawing within two lengths of leader but unable to reach winner thereafter. SHAKA gave an even effort holding third. ADJUTANT (GB) was never a threat while traveling in back of the pack. REAL GOOD MAN (IRE) kept up with the pace early, remained in contention two fences out, then tired going into the last fence.

ENTRY.COMMENT: up with pace early, tired after last fence

ENTRY.NAME: Shaka
ENTRY.COMMENT: even effort holding third

ENTRY.NAME: Chosen Mate (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: wire to wire holding sway over rivals

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHESHIRE RACE 4 3M Timber CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 10000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON OVER TIMBER. Five-year-olds, 160 lbs.; older, 165 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLETCHED led from the start, was overtaken at the last fence, dug in when between horses in a three horse stretch duel and prevailed. CAUSE FOR PARDON stalked the pace, rallied to lead three out, just missed at the wire in a stretch duel. LAP OF THE GODS rated, closed gap three fences out, got up for third in tight three horse finish. BOB'S BAR (IRE) was unhurried in the rear, passed tired ones the final half mile. BROOKLYN SPEIGHTS was never a threat. FASHION LINE lost rider two fences out. BET THE POT raced up with the pace till approaching third last, then tired and was pulled up.

ENTRY.COMMENT: never a threat
